episodes.title: On the Run
episodes.plot: 1994. With the AIDS epidemic reaching fever pitch, Blanca finds purpose working as a nurse's aide at Roosevelt hospital alongside her new love, Christopher. But Blanca's history with a new patient leads to a challenging ordeal. Meanwhile, Lemar shakes up the ballroom community when he becomes father to the unruly House of Khan forcing the House of Evangelista to consider reassembling.

episodes.title: Intervention
episodes.plot: When Pray Tell's alcoholism leads to expected consequences, Blanca stages a much-needed intervention. Meanwhile, Blanca nervously prepares to meet Christopher's parents.

episodes.title: The Trunk
episodes.plot: After she is unjustly arrested, Elektra convinces Blanca to aid in disposing of the trunk in her closet before law enforcement finds it.

episodes.title: Take Me to Church
episodes.plot: After a startling health update, Pray Tell returns home to reconnect with his birth family.

episodes.title: Something Borrowed, Something Blue
episodes.plot: A visit from an old friend complicates Angel and Papi's wedding plans. Meanwhile, Elektra expands her business with the help of her new, shady, associates.

episodes.title: Something Old, Something New
episodes.plot: While the dust settles on their unforeseen life change, Papi adjusts to being a guardian and Angel seeks guidance from an unexpected source.

episodes.title: Series Finale (Part I)
episodes.plot: When Blanca discovers an HIV clinical trial is denying access to people of color, she joins ACT UP in an effort to get Pray Tell and other patients the medication.

episodes.title: Series Finale (Part II)
episodes.plot: When Blanca discovers an HIV clinical trial is denying access to people of color, she joins ACT UP in an effort to get Pray Tell and other patients the medication. Part 2 of the series finale.
